messages.speech: Well, mountain lions, not, no, because although we have a lot of mountain lions, they are cats and you never see them. They kill a lot of animals. Mountain lions, especially, will kill a lot of sheep and baby calves, which we have many where I live, so in that sense, it's a problem. They cause a lot of monetary damage, because a cow costs $500, and they're killing cows. But as far as people go, cats don't really hurt people.
